 \"Hydrolysis of valine nitrile to valine via amide intermediate\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_005\", \"mol_011\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_006\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Pyrolusite\", \"Montmorillonite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"310-330K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"ambient\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Pyrolusite/Montmorillonite\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Hydration, possible wet-dry cycles\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Hydrolysis of nitrile to amide, and then to carboxylic acid, forming valine.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Sutherland-group cyanosulfidic pathways; Powner et al., 2019; theoretical RTIP analyses show lowered activation barriers (Patel et al., 2015).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_005\",\n      \"name\": \"UV-driven reductive homologation of HCN and H2S to valine nitrile\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_003\", \"mol_008\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_005\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Cu(I)/Cu(II)\", \"Phosphate minerals\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"300-330K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"ambient\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Cu(I)/Cu(II)/Phosphate\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"High UV flux\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Photoredox cycles driven by UV and copper ions enable iterative addition, reduction, and branching of nitriles to yield valine nitrile.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Sutherland group, Patel et al., 2015; Powner et al., 2019; cyanosulfidic surface chemistry.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_006\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal reductive amination of alpha-ketoisovalerate to valine\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_002\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_006\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Hydrothermal\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Nickel nanoparticles\", \"Greigite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"80\u00b0C\",\n        \"pressure\": \"5 bar\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Nickel/Greigite\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Alkaline pH 8-11, 72h\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Reductive amination: NH3 reacts with alpha-ketoisovalerate at high pH, nickel/greigite catalysis yields valine.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Kaur et al., 2018; Huber & Wachtershauser, 1997; high-yield, selective hydrothermal pathway.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_007\",\n      \"name\": \"Formation of alpha-ketoisovalerate via hydrothermal carbon fixation\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_011\", \"mol_015\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_007\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Hydrothermal\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Greigite\", \"Pyrrhotite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"350-400K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"high\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Greigite/Pyrrhotite\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Alkaline vent scenario\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Oxidative addition and carboxylation transforms isobutyraldehyde and carbon monoxide into alpha-ketoisovalerate.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Huber & Wachtershauser, 1997; iron-sulfur world theory; Kaur et al., 2018.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_008\",\n      \"name\": \"Strecker-like synthesis in meteoritic aqueous alteration\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_002\", \"mol_011\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_006\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Montmorillonite\", \"Pyrolusite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"275-300K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"ambient\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Montmorillonite/Pyrolusite\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Extended aqueous alteration, parent body simulation\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Standard Strecker reaction under aqueous meteorite-like conditions; proceeds via nitrile and amide then valine (racemic).\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Pizzarello et al., 2008; meteoritic evidence for Strecker pathway during aqueous alteration.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_009\",\n      \"name\": \"Formamide-driven Strecker synthesis\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_002\", \"mol_014\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_006\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"Montmorillonite\", \"Phosphate minerals\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"330-350K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"ambient\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Montmorillonite/Phosphate minerals\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Formamide as solvent enhances conversion\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Formamide lowers activation barriers for hydration and amination, increasing Strecker yield from aldehyde, HCN, and NH3.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Patel et al., 2015; RTIP sampling shows energy lowering, formamide increases Strecker conversion.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_010\",\n      \"name\": \"Supercritical CO2\u2013NH2OH\u2013keto acid system: direct valine synthesis\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_012\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_006\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Hydrothermal\",\n      \"agents\": [\"None\", \"Pressure only\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"333K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"supercritical (150 MPa)\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Pressure (no mineral)\",\n        \"aqueous\": true,\n        \"other\": \"Water phase, 60\u00b0C\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Hydroxylamine reacts with alpha-ketoisovalerate under supercritical CO2 conditions, favoring amino acid formation.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Kakegawa et al., 2017; Wada et al., 2017; pathway modeled after crustal 'soda fountains'.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Classic Strecker Synthesis via Atmospheric Spark Discharge\",\n      \"description\": \"Methane and ammonia spark discharge generates isobutyraldehyde; Strecker reaction yields valine